  "prompt": "Am I pregnant? We used a condom it did not break but I think I was fertile that time. I took nordette though",
  "response": "I'm not a medical professional, but I can try to provide some information that might help you.\n\nIf you used a condom correctly and it did not break, the chances of pregnancy are generally low. Condoms are effective at preventing pregnancy when used properly. Additionally, you mentioned taking Nordette, which is an emergency contraceptive. Emergency contraceptives can reduce the risk of pregnancy if taken soon after unprotected intercourse or contraceptive failure.\n\nFertility can vary, and emergency contraception is most effective when taken as soon as possible after unprotected sex. If you're concerned about the possibility of being pregnant, you might consider taking a pregnancy test to get more certainty. Pregnancy tests are typically accurate when taken at least a week after a missed period.\n\nIf you have specific concerns or need more personalized advice, consulting a healthcare provider would be your best course of action. They can give you accurate information and support based on your individual situation.",
